\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7.17}{\ignorespaces Complex Sinkhorn continuation of a one-dimensional source potential. Two Gaussian-mixture histograms are fixed, $\varepsilon _0=0.55$, and $\varepsilon =\varepsilon _0+i\eta $ is varied for $\eta $ near zero. The left panel shows the centered real perturbation $\Re (\mathrm  {f}_{\varepsilon _0+i\eta }-\mathrm  {f}_{\varepsilon _0})$, while the right panel shows $\Im  \mathrm  {f}_{\varepsilon _0+i\eta }$. The bold black curve is the real-temperature branch $\eta =0$; colored curves follow the local branch for negative $\eta $ in blue, positive $\eta $ in red, and intermediate values in violet. The faint red and blue silhouettes show the source and target histograms.}}{125}{figure.7.17}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:sinkhorn-complex-epsilon-continuation}{{7.17}{125}{Complex Sinkhorn continuation of a one-dimensional source potential. Two Gaussian-mixture histograms are fixed, $\epsilon _0=0.55$, and $\epsilon =\epsilon _0+i\eta $ is varied for $\eta $ near zero. The left panel shows the centered real perturbation $\Re (\fD _{\epsilon _0+i\eta }-\fD _{\epsilon _0})$, while the right panel shows $\Im \fD _{\epsilon _0+i\eta }$. The bold black curve is the real-temperature branch $\eta =0$; colored curves follow the local branch for negative $\eta $ in blue, positive $\eta $ in red, and intermediate values in violet. The faint red and blue silhouettes show the source and target histograms}{figure.7.17}{}}
