\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9.4}{\ignorespaces Two-dimensional partial optimal transport between a red cat-shaped indicator measure and a blue annulus indicator measure. Both supports are sampled by farthest-point sampling. In each panel, saturated points are the active source and target marginals of the optimal partial plan, while pale points are available mass left unmatched. Thin black segments show a farthest-spaced subsample of transported source locations connected to the dominant target selected by the plan. As the prescribed mass decreases, the active regions contract to the nearest compatible pieces of the two shapes.}}{152}{figure.9.4}\protected@file@percent }
