\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {12.3}{\ignorespaces Balanced and unbalanced Sinkhorn-barycenter interpolations between two one-dimensional Gaussian mixtures with swapped modal masses. The balanced row conserves total mass, so excess mass from the dominant left mode must move along the line toward the dominant right target mode, producing transient mass in the middle. The unbalanced row uses KL-relaxed marginal constraints; mass can be attenuated near overrepresented modes and recreated near underrepresented modes, giving a reaction--transport interpolation closer to the Wasserstein--Fisher--Rao intuition.}}{208}{figure.12.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:dynamic-unbalanced-geodesic}{{12.3}{208}{Balanced and unbalanced Sinkhorn-barycenter interpolations between two one-dimensional Gaussian mixtures with swapped modal masses. The balanced row conserves total mass, so excess mass from the dominant left mode must move along the line toward the dominant right target mode, producing transient mass in the middle. The unbalanced row uses KL-relaxed marginal constraints; mass can be attenuated near overrepresented modes and recreated near underrepresented modes, giving a reaction--transport interpolation closer to the Wasserstein--Fisher--Rao intuition}{figure.12.3}{}}
