\newlabel{fig:generative-diffusion-1d-forward-backward}{{14.2}{245}{One-dimensional diffusion bridge for a Gaussian-mixture data law. The forward path $Z_t=(1-t)X+tY$ smooths the red data density toward a blue Gaussian endpoint. Reversing the probability-flow ODE transports a denser set of blue noise samples back toward the data modes, making the splitting of trajectories across mixture components visible}{figure.14.2}{}}
