\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {14.7}{\ignorespaces Forward moment-measure construction in one dimension. The top row uses $u(x)=x^2/2$, so $\rho _u$ and $\mathfrak  M(u)$ are both standard Gaussian and $u'(x)=x$. The bottom row uses $u(x)=x^2/2+0.18\,x^4/4+0.92\,x$, which tilts the log-concave source and produces a nonlinear monotone map. In both cases the blue push-forward has barycenter zero, illustrating the identity $\DOTSI \intop \ilimits@ y\,\mathrm  {d}\mathfrak  M(u)(y)=0$.}}{252}{figure.14.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:moment-measure-forward-map}{{14.7}{252}{Forward moment-measure construction in one dimension. The top row uses $u(x)=x^2/2$, so $\rho _u$ and $\mathfrak M(u)$ are both standard Gaussian and $u'(x)=x$. The bottom row uses $u(x)=x^2/2+0.18\,x^4/4+0.92\,x$, which tilts the log-concave source and produces a nonlinear monotone map. In both cases the blue push-forward has barycenter zero, illustrating the identity $\int y\,\d \mathfrak M(u)(y)=0$}{figure.14.7}{}}
