\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {14.9}{\ignorespaces Gaussian closures of transport dynamics between two overlapping anisotropic Gaussians. The left panel is the exact $W_2$ Gaussian geodesic. The middle panel shows a regularized Sinkhorn-style closure, where the same mean path is accompanied by inflated intermediate covariances. The right panel shows a drifting-style closure with a curved mean path and moment-matched covariance ellipses. These finite-dimensional pictures keep only means and covariances, and therefore discard higher-order shape information that would be created by a genuinely nonlinear velocity field.}}{257}{figure.14.9}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:gradflow-gaussian-closure}{{14.9}{257}{Gaussian closures of transport dynamics between two overlapping anisotropic Gaussians. The left panel is the exact $W_2$ Gaussian geodesic. The middle panel shows a regularized Sinkhorn-style closure, where the same mean path is accompanied by inflated intermediate covariances. The right panel shows a drifting-style closure with a curved mean path and moment-matched covariance ellipses. These finite-dimensional pictures keep only means and covariances, and therefore discard higher-order shape information that would be created by a genuinely nonlinear velocity field}{figure.14.9}{}}
